<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: About PvP Editorial - Quote of the Day</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Geiger">Geiger</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:22 a.m. 10/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: About PvP Editorial - Quote of the Day<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=427" TARGET=_self>About PvP Editorial</A> (Kain)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I Decided to implement a PvP Quote of the day. Everyone is welcome to nominate something said (Hopefully we have enough good things said, at least for a while) I had to quote that one. Picture all the PvE advocates squirming. :)

<P>&gt; The editorial is right on. The ideas about restricting the
<BR>&gt; playerkilling are awesome. I liked them all except having a Safe
<BR>&gt; Zone in the middle of town...that would not be cool (Fountain or
<BR>&gt; something of the like)but having it at a shrine or church is
<BR>&gt; acceptable. Also, I too, noticed EQ being focused more on Non
<BR>&gt; PvP gameplay....how can you be an evil character...and not kill
<BR>&gt; other characters at free will? I know that you can kill NPC's,
<BR>&gt; but that's still not the same. I hope Verant Interactive Inc.
<BR>&gt; considers and implements some of these ideas....that would help
<BR>&gt; make EQ a great ORPG.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
